uedToken` persistence, RS256 JWT claim creation, `/oauth/token` authorization_code handling, and focused unit/E2E coverage for single-use exchange and invalid cases.\nprisma/seed.mjs:241:export async function seedOAuthClientDefaults(client = prisma) {\nprisma/seed.mjs:481:  await seedOAuthClientDefaults();\ndocs/exec-plans/completed/027-mcp-resource-prompt-domain-schema.md:46:- Add Prisma models/migration for direct resources, resource templates, prompt definitions, prompt arguments/messages, completion candidates, and permission-ready IDs.\ndocs/exec-plans/completed/027-mcp-resource-prompt-domain-schema.md:54:- OAuth permission enforcement.\ndocs/product-specs/rest-mock-api.md:18:- `GET /rest/tools` with a valid OAuth Bearer token returns only enabled endpoints included in the token's endpoint permissions.\ndocs/product-specs/rest-mock-api.md:27:  - `403 { \"error\": \"forbidden\", \"message\": \"Bearer token does not grant permission for this endpoint.\", \"tool\": \"<tool name>\" }`\ndocs/exec-plans/completed/025-inspector-compatibility-pack.md:25:    \"npm run test:e2e -- tests/e2e/mcp-initialize-list.spec.ts tests/e2e/oauth-code-token.spec.ts tests/e2e/oauth-discovery.spec.ts tests/e2e/oauth-permissions.spec.ts tests/e2e/rest-tools-list.spec.ts tests/e2e/rest-tools-call.spec.ts tests/e2e/operator-config.spec.ts\",\ndocs/exec-plans/completed/025-inspector-compatibility-pack.md:100:- `npm run test:e2e -- tests/e2e/mcp-initialize-list.spec.ts tests/e2e/oauth-code-token.spec.ts tests/e2e/oauth-discovery.spec.ts tests/e2e/oauth-permissions.spec.ts tests/e2e/rest-tools-list.spec.ts tests/e2e/rest-tools-call.spec.ts tests/e2e/operator-config.spec.ts`\ndocs/PRODUCT_SENSE.md:11:MCP client and AI-agent developers need a configurable remote server that behaves enough like a real MCP server to prove connection, auth, token, permission, and tool-call behavior before integrating with production systems.\ndocs/PRODUCT_SENSE.md:14:Remote MCP adoption is moving auth, transport, and permission bugs into client integration work. A public mock server gives teams a repeatable target for manual testing, automated E2E checks, demos, and negative-path validation.\ndocs/PRODUCT_SENSE.md:21:- endpoint permissions are visible, selectable, and enforced\ndocs/PRODUCT_SENSE.md:32:- issue mock OAuth tokens with endpoint-level permissions through browser consent or non-interactive client credentials\ndocs/PRODUCT_SENSE.md:33:- create mock OAuth authorization codes through browser login and consent with explicit endpoint permission selection\ndocs/PRODUCT_SENSE.md:53:- OAuth consent can select endpoints, exchange a single-use code for a JWT with endpoint permission claims, allow selected tools, deny unselected tools with 403, and return 401 after revocation\ndocs/PRODUCT_SENSE.md:54:- OAuth Bearer runtime enforcement applies the same endpoint permission resolver to MCP and REST calls while leaving no-auth and Basic callers unrestricted by OAuth permissions\ndocs/PRODUCT_SENSE.md:56:- token and audit screens show enough evidence to debug a client test, including token status, claims, endpoint permissions, revocation, and endpoint delete success/failure without stored secrets\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
